WEBVTT

00:01.084 --> 00:03.295
Adult Adam: Back in the '80s,
"Airplane!" was

00:03.295 --> 00:04.338
the pinnacle sky‐high spoof.

00:04.338 --> 00:07.382
And Leon's
getting larger!

00:07.382 --> 00:09.843
It was packed with
so many laughs, gags, and puns,

00:09.843 --> 00:11.094
you couldn't keep up.

00:11.094 --> 00:12.554
And guess who knew it
line‐by‐line.

00:12.554 --> 00:14.598
Surely,
you can't be serious.

00:14.598 --> 00:15.807
I am serious.

00:15.807 --> 00:17.059
And don't call me Shirley.

00:17.059 --> 00:19.228
It's an adverb, but he thinks
it's a ladies' name!

00:19.228 --> 00:20.604
It can't get
any better!

00:20.604 --> 00:22.940
Look how happy this movie
makes you. It's so cute.

00:22.940 --> 00:24.441
You're the cute one.

00:24.441 --> 00:26.485
If you were a board game,
you'd be Cutes N' Ladders.

00:26.485 --> 00:28.695
If you were a cereal,
you'd be Cutie Pebbles.

00:28.695 --> 00:31.281
If you were a mathematician,
you'd be Sir Isaac Cute‐on.

00:31.281 --> 00:32.908
Enough!
You're both disgusting!

00:32.908 --> 00:35.827
Ren and I are so in sync,
we even finish each other's...

00:35.827 --> 00:37.538
Sentences.
...word groupings.
[ Chuckles ] That counts.

00:37.538 --> 00:38.789
Young, new love.

00:38.789 --> 00:40.541
So very, very stupid.

00:40.541 --> 00:42.376
Yep, when you've been together
as long as we have,

00:42.376 --> 00:43.877
there's no need
to prove anything.

00:43.877 --> 00:45.128
Last night,
we went to dinner

00:45.128 --> 00:46.547
and didn't say
a single word grouping.

00:46.547 --> 00:48.465
Listen up,
sweet pits of my peach.

00:48.465 --> 00:50.968
What's the greatest thing
to ever happen to this family?

00:50.968 --> 00:53.178
When Barry fell
in Aunt Dotty's open grave.

00:53.178 --> 00:54.221
[ Laughing ]
Best day of our lives.

00:54.221 --> 00:56.181
We were grieving,
and I brought joy.

00:56.181 --> 00:58.392
Even better!
We're flying to Miami!

00:58.392 --> 01:00.269
Oh‐ho‐ho‐ho‐ho!
[ Laughs ]

01:00.269 --> 01:02.354
♪ Come on, shake your body,
baby, do the conga ♪

01:02.354 --> 01:04.356
♪ I know you can't control
yourself any longer ♪

01:04.356 --> 01:06.233
Come on, Erica, take on
the rhythm of the night!

01:06.233 --> 01:08.443
Pass. We are gonna spend
our last few days

01:08.443 --> 01:10.696
before college starts together,
and that's that.

01:10.696 --> 01:12.364
I had a feeling
you were gonna say that,

01:12.364 --> 01:14.366
which is why
Geoff's invited, too.

01:14.366 --> 01:15.909
I'm finally
a part of the family!

01:15.909 --> 01:18.537
After years of personal
indignities, I feel so special!

01:18.537 --> 01:20.622
Don't. Because Brea and Ren
are also in.

01:20.622 --> 01:21.707
Noyce!

01:21.707 --> 01:23.166
Ren, this is
the perfect time

01:23.166 --> 01:24.626
for us to get back
on the same...

01:24.626 --> 01:25.669
Page!
...airplane!

01:25.669 --> 01:26.878
What's up with you?!

01:26.878 --> 01:28.297
Oh, whoa, whoa, whoa.

01:28.297 --> 01:30.090
There is no way that Dad
would pay for all of us

01:30.090 --> 01:31.842
to fly
and stay in a hotel.

01:31.842 --> 01:34.094
What's your scheme,
Blondie?
No scheme.

01:34.094 --> 01:36.513
Remember when I screamed
at that woman at the Sheraton

01:36.513 --> 01:38.473
because the complimentary
champagne was too cold?

01:38.473 --> 01:40.726
Mandy from Fort Wayne
cried so much.

01:40.726 --> 01:43.645
The manager gave me 50 free
nights to leave the premises.

01:43.645 --> 01:45.314
So we all win.

01:45.314 --> 01:46.523
Yes!

01:46.523 --> 01:49.568
I get to do "Airplane!" bits
on an actual airplane!

01:49.568 --> 01:51.737
"Looks like I picked the wrong
week to quit sniffing glue."

01:51.737 --> 01:52.863
[ Chuckles ]
That's one of them.

01:52.863 --> 01:54.531
[ "Conga" plays ]

01:54.531 --> 01:56.366
♪ Come on, shake your body,
baby, do the conga ♪

01:56.366 --> 01:58.535
♪ I know you can't control
yourself any longer ♪

01:58.535 --> 02:01.204
Come on, kids. Feel the pulsing
rhythm of Mama's hips!

02:01.204 --> 02:02.748
Whoo!
Ohh!

02:02.748 --> 02:03.582
Ow!
Oh, sorry!

02:06.585 --> 02:09.588
♪♪

02:09.588 --> 02:12.049
Adult Adam:
It was the end of summer,
1980‐something,

02:12.049 --> 02:13.800
and before we took
to the skies,

02:13.800 --> 02:16.637
there were a few things
to take care of on the ground.

02:16.637 --> 02:20.724
♪♪

02:20.724 --> 02:22.851
Thank you so much
for packing in here

02:22.851 --> 02:24.561
under my watchful eye.

02:24.561 --> 02:25.771
You'll be happy
to know

02:25.771 --> 02:27.314
this is a bag
full of hand weights.

02:27.314 --> 02:28.523
[ Fabric rips ]

02:28.523 --> 02:29.608
Damn it!

02:29.608 --> 02:31.735
Idiot, these bags
are for clothes.

02:31.735 --> 02:34.446
That's why my fanny pack
has everything I need ‐‐

02:34.446 --> 02:36.615
two bikinis, my scrunchy,
and browning oil.

02:36.615 --> 02:38.784
Someone's forgetting about
the cool Latin nights.

02:38.784 --> 02:40.243
And that right there

02:40.243 --> 02:42.120
is why I've gone ahead
and packed for you.

02:42.120 --> 02:44.956
These bags and the other 12 in
the car should keep you covered.

02:44.956 --> 02:46.249
This one's empty.

02:46.249 --> 02:47.918
That is for
all the hotel freebies

02:47.918 --> 02:49.753
that it is our divine right
to take.

02:49.753 --> 02:51.213
Like shampoo?
Obviously.

02:51.213 --> 02:53.382
But I'm talking
so much more.

02:53.382 --> 02:56.968
Robes, towels,
the pens, stationery,

02:56.968 --> 02:58.887
batteries from the remote,
the remote,

02:58.887 --> 03:00.347
pillows, hair dryer,

03:00.347 --> 03:03.016
iron, clock radio,

03:03.016 --> 03:05.435
and curtains,
both window and shower.

03:05.435 --> 03:06.812
Why not take the TV,
too?

03:06.812 --> 03:08.689
Because that's stealing,
Erica.

03:08.689 --> 03:09.856
What the hell's
going on?

03:09.856 --> 03:12.109
I've been waiting in the car
for 16 minutes.

03:12.109 --> 03:14.111
Murray, the flight doesn't leave
for six hours.

03:14.111 --> 03:15.946
We're not even in the air
half that long.

03:15.946 --> 03:17.948
Thank you,
Amilio Airhead.

03:17.948 --> 03:20.617
Have you taken into
consideration the traffic,

03:20.617 --> 03:23.036
the parking, the shuttle?
I guess not.

03:23.036 --> 03:25.163
That's the smartest thing
you've ever said.

03:25.163 --> 03:26.665
I'll be waiting
in the car.

03:27.624 --> 03:30.043
This trip is gonna be
so special. [ Chuckles ]

03:30.043 --> 03:31.670
How special?

03:31.670 --> 03:34.256
Why did you pack me
a cocktail dress?

03:34.256 --> 03:35.340
Just in case.

03:35.340 --> 03:36.299
Just in case what?

03:36.299 --> 03:39.344
In case, uh,
Edward James Olmos

03:39.344 --> 03:41.847
invites us for Mojitos
on his cigarette boat.

03:41.847 --> 03:43.598
[ Chuckles ]
You got to keep an open mind.

03:43.598 --> 03:45.559
The only thing open
are my eyes.

03:45.559 --> 03:46.935
You're definitely
up to something,

03:46.935 --> 03:48.520
and I'm gonna
find out what.

03:48.520 --> 03:49.855
[ Car horn honking ]

03:49.855 --> 03:52.149
Yeah, Dad did an angry
8‐point turn in the driveway.

03:52.149 --> 03:53.275
He's ready.

03:53.275 --> 03:55.068
Packing may not have been
our bag,

03:55.068 --> 03:56.987
but we were on our way to...

03:56.987 --> 04:00.949
♪♪

04:00.949 --> 04:04.244
We were all super excited
to go to Miami ‐‐

04:04.244 --> 04:07.038
except for my dad, who was
totally terrified of flying.

04:07.038 --> 04:08.665
How do they get all that metal
up in the air?

04:08.665 --> 04:10.167
It makes no sense.

04:10.167 --> 04:12.627
It also doesn't make any sense
how much you're sweating.

04:12.627 --> 04:15.297
Ha! He thinks
we're all gonna die. This guy.

04:15.297 --> 04:17.174
If the plane doesn't
kill you, I will.

04:17.174 --> 04:19.509
Looks like it's time for someone
to take their sleepy pills.

04:19.509 --> 04:20.927
But that's
my allergy meds.

04:20.927 --> 04:22.721
What happens
if I run into some buckwheat

04:22.721 --> 04:23.930
and my face gets puffy?

04:23.930 --> 04:26.433
More of you to love,
schmoopaloo. [ Chuckles ]

04:26.433 --> 04:27.851
Wow.
So much has happened,

04:27.851 --> 04:29.770
and we haven't even made it
to the ticket counter.

04:29.770 --> 04:30.771
This is nothing.

04:30.771 --> 04:32.105
Good rule of thumb ‐‐

04:32.105 --> 04:34.775
as the plane goes higher,
our appeal goes lower.

04:34.775 --> 04:36.735
Hey, guys.
What the hell is this?

04:36.735 --> 04:38.820
I thought it'd be fun to dress
like Crockett from "Miami Vice."

04:38.820 --> 04:40.322
I'm Crockett
from "Miami Vice."

04:40.322 --> 04:41.406
Okay.
I'll be Tubbs, then.

04:41.406 --> 04:42.365
Ooh,
I like Tubbs.

04:42.365 --> 04:44.326
You do?
Switch it. I'm Tubbs.

04:44.326 --> 04:46.620
Fine, Crockett it is.
Yeah,
Crockett is the man.

04:46.620 --> 04:48.455
No, I'm the man!
I have to be Crockett.

04:48.455 --> 04:50.290
Back to Tubbs.
Not fair.
I have to be Tubbs.

04:50.290 --> 04:51.833
Can you just tell me
who you want to be?

04:51.833 --> 04:54.419
I will be Crockett and Tubbs,
also known as Crubbs.

04:54.419 --> 04:55.796
Great.
Great,
and I'll be sitting

04:55.796 --> 04:57.172
in the back of the plane
with you, confused.

04:57.172 --> 04:58.298
Not in the back.

04:58.298 --> 05:00.300
For my special lady,
only first class will do.

05:00.300 --> 05:01.968
Barry, is this
because I told you

05:01.968 --> 05:03.970
I flew to St. Barts
in my parents' private plane?

05:03.970 --> 05:05.055
Did you?
[ Chuckles ]

05:05.055 --> 05:06.848
I'd already forgotten
you spent your summer

05:06.848 --> 05:08.350
and a lifetime
in the lap of luxury.

05:08.350 --> 05:10.101
I'm telling you
coach is fine.

05:10.101 --> 05:12.813
See, I'm gonna be a doctor
for the 76ers,

05:12.813 --> 05:14.481
occasionally
coming off the bench

05:14.481 --> 05:16.399
to windmill jam
in Karl Malone's face.

05:16.399 --> 05:18.401
My life will be one
of pampered excess,

05:18.401 --> 05:21.530
and my classy lady
doesn't sit in coach

05:21.530 --> 05:22.989
with the sky trash.

05:22.989 --> 05:24.324
Aww.
[ Chuckles ]

05:26.159 --> 05:29.079
Wait, you got us tickets
on Oceanic?

05:29.079 --> 05:31.081
Yes, Murray. You told me
to get the cheapest.

05:31.081 --> 05:32.499
Yeah,
I meant with yogurt,

05:32.499 --> 05:34.960
not taking a flying go‐kart
to your cousin's thing.

05:34.960 --> 05:37.504
Shh! The kids don't know
that's why we're going.

05:37.504 --> 05:38.463
I don't even know
why we're going.

05:38.463 --> 05:41.174
I told you, it's Mitzy's son's
Bar Mitzvah.

05:41.174 --> 05:43.176
And once Bradley
becomes a man,

05:43.176 --> 05:45.470
I will become the object
of Mitzy's envy

05:45.470 --> 05:47.681
because my family
is so attractive.

05:47.681 --> 05:50.517
You know, once the kids find out
you're dragging them to Miami

05:50.517 --> 05:52.894
for a religious thing,
they're not gonna be happy.

05:52.894 --> 05:54.938
Oh, but they will.
[ Chuckles ]

05:54.938 --> 05:56.147
They will.

05:56.147 --> 05:57.566
You see?
Something's up.

05:57.566 --> 05:59.109
Whenever Mom has
a secret plan,

05:59.109 --> 06:00.569
she always moves her fingers
by her mouth,

06:00.569 --> 06:01.903
like a demented gerbil.

06:01.903 --> 06:04.322
Well, maybe the secret plan
is something very cool.

06:04.322 --> 06:05.949
What are you
talking about?

06:05.949 --> 06:07.659
I accidentally hinted
to Geoff

06:07.659 --> 06:09.494
that we were gonna sit
front row

06:09.494 --> 06:12.289
at a jai alai match
with Miami Sound Machine.

06:12.289 --> 06:14.082
Why would anyone believe
those words?

06:14.082 --> 06:17.043
Because they know their mama
would do anything for them.

06:17.043 --> 06:20.005
They'll be all dressed up
and excited, and then, boom!

06:20.005 --> 06:21.631
Everyone's lifting me up
on a chair.

06:21.631 --> 06:23.508
Your mom let slip
she has a big surprise.

06:23.508 --> 06:25.135
Now, I'm not gonna say
a word,

06:25.135 --> 06:26.845
but it would be a high lie
[jai alai]

06:26.845 --> 06:28.179
for me to say
I'm not excited

06:28.179 --> 06:30.015
to meet
a certain Latin songstress,

06:30.015 --> 06:32.058
of whom
I'm a huge Este‐fan.

06:32.058 --> 06:33.059
Holy crap.

06:33.059 --> 06:34.352
Are we going
to a jai alai match

06:34.352 --> 06:36.563
with Gloria Estefan
and Miami Sound Machine?

06:36.563 --> 06:38.023
No. Maybe. Yes.

06:38.023 --> 06:39.566
Damn it, Geoff!
Be stronger!

06:39.566 --> 06:42.193
Once we're in that sweltering,
windowless ballroom,

06:42.193 --> 06:44.404
they'll have a blast
and forget all about

06:44.404 --> 06:47.365
my phony promises
of skin and sand.

06:47.365 --> 06:48.992
You know, the pills
must be kicking in.

06:48.992 --> 06:50.785
[ Chuckles ]
'Cause I don't care.

06:50.785 --> 06:53.204
My mom wouldn't build a trip
around some weird sport

06:53.204 --> 06:54.706
and a Latin pop orchestra.

06:54.706 --> 06:57.500
Geoff, you're in charge of
getting to the bottom of this.

06:57.500 --> 07:00.337
On it. Also, what a great start
to a relaxing vacation.

07:00.337 --> 07:03.340
Hi. Barry Goldberg,
AKA "Crubbs."

07:03.340 --> 07:05.425
Can I just say
that is an ugly vest,

07:05.425 --> 07:07.844
but somehow you manage
to pull it off.
Thank you?

07:07.844 --> 07:10.138
My girlfriend and I are ticketed
to be in steerage,

07:10.138 --> 07:11.765
but we've been apart
all summer,

07:11.765 --> 07:13.558
and I want this trip
to be truly special.

07:13.558 --> 07:15.268
That is so adorable!

07:15.268 --> 07:17.145
So, if you can get us
an upgrade,

07:17.145 --> 07:19.272
I would sincerely
appreciate it.

07:19.272 --> 07:21.566
[ Keyboard clacking ]
You're in luck.
Two seats left.

07:21.566 --> 07:24.444
Yes! Eat my dust,
second‐class garbage people.

07:24.444 --> 07:25.904
That'll be $5,000.

07:25.904 --> 07:27.739
What?!
Bar,
I told you it's fine.

07:27.739 --> 07:29.199
It's not, okay?

07:29.199 --> 07:31.660
You deserve first class.
It's your birthright.

07:31.660 --> 07:34.371
As it's mine to visit
the captain in the cockpit

07:34.371 --> 07:36.748
so we can acknowledge each other
as alpha males

07:36.748 --> 07:38.958
and he can let me flip switches
and make bomber noises.

07:38.958 --> 07:40.960
Come on, everyone.
We're heading to the gate.

07:40.960 --> 07:42.837
Oh, and I just want to
double‐check

07:42.837 --> 07:45.298
that the three of you told Pops
we did not need him

07:45.298 --> 07:46.758
to drive us to the airport.

07:46.758 --> 07:48.426
Yes.
Uh‐huh.
We said those words
exactly.

07:48.426 --> 07:49.719
They had not.

07:49.719 --> 07:51.513
Hey,
don't take too much time!

07:51.513 --> 07:53.348
You'd hate to miss
your flight!

07:53.348 --> 07:54.808
Did everyone go potty?

07:54.808 --> 07:56.267
Cargo hold's all clear,
Mrs. G.

07:56.267 --> 07:58.853
Brea? Ren?
Pishy and boom, hmm?

07:58.853 --> 08:00.271
Trust me,
the less time you spend

08:00.271 --> 08:01.690
in a sky toilet,
the better.

08:01.690 --> 08:03.066
Um...
What's happening?

08:03.066 --> 08:05.110
What's happening was
it was time to board.

08:05.110 --> 08:09.072
♪♪

08:09.072 --> 08:11.950
Flying in the '80s was a little
different than it is now.

08:11.950 --> 08:13.118
First,
there was no security.

08:13.118 --> 08:14.452
What's this?

08:14.452 --> 08:16.204
Nunchucks?
Throwing stars?

08:16.204 --> 08:17.247
Rope dart?

08:18.248 --> 08:20.041
Cool.
[ Zipper closes ]

08:20.041 --> 08:21.710
Have a great flight.
Thanks.

08:21.710 --> 08:23.545
Then there was getting on
the actual plane.

08:23.545 --> 08:26.089
It was...
well, less organized.

08:26.089 --> 08:28.550
[ Amplified ]
Three...two...one...

08:28.550 --> 08:29.718
board!

08:29.718 --> 08:31.720
Get low
and use your elbows!

08:31.720 --> 08:34.597
Of course, my mom
usually got us on first,

08:34.597 --> 08:36.099
and once we were on,

08:36.099 --> 08:38.643
that's when
the real adventure began.

08:38.643 --> 08:41.062
[ Scoffs ]
It won't recline. Ugh!

08:41.062 --> 08:42.021
Oh.
Mine won't, either.

08:42.021 --> 08:44.190
Unacceptable
for my swanky angel!

08:45.233 --> 08:46.776
Hey, we're switching,
okay?

08:46.776 --> 08:48.069
These seats won't go back.

08:48.069 --> 08:49.404
You're made
of Silly Putty,

08:49.404 --> 08:51.239
so your body can fit
in any container.

08:51.239 --> 08:51.990
No way.

08:51.990 --> 08:53.283
Accommodate me,

08:53.283 --> 08:56.119
or I'll do something
very Barry‐like.

08:56.119 --> 08:59.205
It's okay. I'd rather
not see, hear, or smell
whatever that means.

08:59.205 --> 09:01.124
Gah!

09:01.124 --> 09:03.126
Isn't this sumptuous,
baby?

09:03.126 --> 09:05.545
Now my jacked thighs
can breathe.

09:05.545 --> 09:08.381
Are these seats
still not reclining properly?

09:08.381 --> 09:10.675
We have two available
in first class.

09:10.675 --> 09:11.509
Come with me.

09:11.509 --> 09:12.552
Oh. Wow.

09:12.552 --> 09:13.636
What?

09:13.636 --> 09:14.804
This can't be happening.

09:14.804 --> 09:16.973
And yet it is.
Have fun back here.

09:16.973 --> 09:18.141
This can't get
any worse.

09:18.141 --> 09:19.601
I think
I'm in the middle there.

09:19.601 --> 09:22.395
Damn it! There goes
my natural spreading room.

09:22.395 --> 09:24.355
While Barry's upgrade
got denied,

09:24.355 --> 09:25.899
Brea and I
were getting comfy.

09:25.899 --> 09:27.150
So, this trip.

09:27.150 --> 09:28.526
Just me and you.

09:28.526 --> 09:30.361
I mean, I know we spend
a lot of time together,

09:30.361 --> 09:33.114
but this is gonna be
all day, every day.

09:33.114 --> 09:35.158
You know, maybe there's
still stuff that we don't
know about each other.

09:35.158 --> 09:36.785
Maybe.
Check this out.

09:36.785 --> 09:38.828
Dan? Can I ask you
a question?

09:38.828 --> 09:40.246
Question.
What is it?

09:40.246 --> 09:42.207
It's a sentence that's worded
to elicit information,

09:42.207 --> 09:43.917
but that's not important
right now.

09:43.917 --> 09:45.502
Have you ever been
to a Turkish prison?

09:45.502 --> 09:46.461
The "Airplane!" movie.

09:47.754 --> 09:49.964
I can't wait to attend
to your every need.

09:52.092 --> 09:54.135
[ Gasps ] Why is there
a guy on the wing?!

09:54.135 --> 09:55.512
He's a mechanic.

09:55.512 --> 09:57.263
Hey!
The plane is broken!

09:57.263 --> 09:58.890
We won't make it!

09:58.890 --> 09:59.891
Don't worry, everyone.

09:59.891 --> 10:01.643
He's just
a nervous flier, um,

10:01.643 --> 10:03.603
with a bit
of a nervous tummy.

10:03.603 --> 10:06.147
So let's keep
the mid‐cabin lavatory

10:06.147 --> 10:08.233
available to him
at all times.

10:08.233 --> 10:09.275
Who is this lady?

10:09.275 --> 10:10.693
In short, the last person

10:10.693 --> 10:12.403
you'd ever want to be
on your flight.

10:12.403 --> 10:16.449
♪♪

10:16.449 --> 10:19.327
Naturally, flying with
my family was no joyride.
[ Ding ]

10:19.327 --> 10:21.371
A Chablis for my husband,
please.

10:21.371 --> 10:22.789
[ Ding ]
Especially
for the flight attendants.

10:22.789 --> 10:24.749
Is this plane really flying
to Miami?

10:24.749 --> 10:26.209
[ Ding ]

10:26.209 --> 10:27.877
We've got clearance,
Clarence.

10:27.877 --> 10:30.171
What's the vector, Victor?
Roger, Roger.

10:30.171 --> 10:31.756
[ Ding ]
Would you let
the captain know

10:31.756 --> 10:33.174
I'd like to drop by
the cockpit?

10:33.174 --> 10:34.384
[ Ding ]

10:34.384 --> 10:36.386
You're gonna have to deal
with this baby's mother.

10:36.386 --> 10:39.597
[ Scoffs ]
I got her to stop crying,
and yet I'm the bad guy?

10:39.597 --> 10:40.598
[ Ding ]

10:40.598 --> 10:42.559
Blink once
if my mother is forcing you

10:42.559 --> 10:43.977
to take part in her scheme.

10:43.977 --> 10:46.104
[ Ding ]
Do you like movies
about gladiators?

10:46.104 --> 10:47.480
[ Laughs ]

10:47.480 --> 10:49.107
[ Ding ]

10:49.107 --> 10:50.692
That lady has
the drink cart again.

10:50.692 --> 10:52.443
Drink up.

10:52.443 --> 10:54.737
Yep, it usually got so bad,
[ Ding ]
[ Ding ]

10:54.737 --> 10:57.365
[ Dinging ]
those poor sky stewards
had no choice but to do this.

10:57.365 --> 10:58.783
Our apologies.

10:58.783 --> 11:01.536
The call button system
has been disconnected.

11:01.536 --> 11:04.205
Also, I know it seems like
we've been flying for hours,

11:04.205 --> 11:06.291
but we'll be taking off
shortly.

11:06.291 --> 11:08.459
This really is
a discount airline.

11:08.459 --> 11:10.211
I'm gonna go
speak to the captain

11:10.211 --> 11:11.796
about some
flight vouchers.

11:11.796 --> 11:13.464
Okay, my dad's alone
and loopy.

11:13.464 --> 11:14.674
Go pump him for intel.

11:14.674 --> 11:16.176
Erica,
is this really necessary?

11:16.176 --> 11:18.469
Yes. I mean, this whole trip
makes no sense.

11:18.469 --> 11:20.555
When does my mom just
give us stuff out of the blue?

11:20.555 --> 11:22.390
Adam has
like 5,000 toys,

11:22.390 --> 11:24.184
Barry has every sporting good
known to man,

11:24.184 --> 11:26.477
and you have more musical
instruments than you even
know how to play.

11:26.477 --> 11:27.478
What's a zither?

11:27.478 --> 11:29.522
Something I need
to be happy. Go!

11:29.522 --> 11:31.774
Erica knew
my mom was hiding something,

11:31.774 --> 11:34.235
and lucky for Geoff,
my dad was on something.

11:34.235 --> 11:35.612
Hey, Mr. Goldberg.
How goes it?

11:35.612 --> 11:36.613
So sleepy.

11:36.613 --> 11:38.323
Okay, you seem
incredibly drugged,

11:38.323 --> 11:39.908
so I'll just cut
right to the chase.

11:39.908 --> 11:42.160
Your daughter is a little bit
suspicious about this trip.

11:42.160 --> 11:43.328
Bradley's a man now.

11:43.328 --> 11:45.371
Wait, like,
Cousin Mitzy's Bradley?

11:45.371 --> 11:46.915
[ Whispering ]
Bar Mitzvah boy.

11:46.915 --> 11:48.249
Is that why
we're going to Miami?

11:48.249 --> 11:49.959
We'll all be
dancing the hora.

11:49.959 --> 11:51.753
Geoffrey, can I speak to you
alone, please?

11:51.753 --> 11:52.503
No, that's okay.

11:52.503 --> 11:53.296
And it's happening!

11:56.257 --> 11:58.843
Do you know what the
most important thing
in the world to me is?

11:58.843 --> 12:00.887
Mrs. G, as you know,
I'm incredibly claustrophobic.

12:00.887 --> 12:02.263
Family.

12:02.263 --> 12:04.599
The family that
you are now a part of.

12:04.599 --> 12:06.351
There's not a lot of air
in here. Throat's getting tight.

12:06.351 --> 12:08.311
[ Toilet flushes ]
Oh, no! I just flushed
the toilet with my foot!

12:08.311 --> 12:11.940
You have to promise
to keep my secret.

12:11.940 --> 12:13.983
Secrets are what hold
a family together

12:13.983 --> 12:15.401
and make it strong.

12:15.401 --> 12:16.611
You know what else is strong,
is your grip.

12:16.611 --> 12:18.071
Shh.
Yep.

12:19.489 --> 12:21.491
[ Chuckles ]
Tummy trouble for this one.

12:22.951 --> 12:24.827
What the hell was that?

12:24.827 --> 12:26.788
Your mom helped me
through some bathroom
issues, and nothing more!

12:26.788 --> 12:28.289
[ Intercom chimes ]

12:28.289 --> 12:29.749
Captain Roger: Hey, folks.
This is your captain.

12:29.749 --> 12:31.459
There's a large storm brewing.

12:31.459 --> 12:34.587
It's gonna get bumpy,
so hang on to those cigarettes.

12:34.587 --> 12:37.715
Adult Adam:
Despite the rough air, we were
finally ready for takeoff.

12:37.715 --> 12:39.884
That's right.
And knowing my family,
it was gonna get even bumpier.

12:43.763 --> 12:46.641
♪♪

12:46.641 --> 12:48.726
The Goldbergs were in the air.

12:48.726 --> 12:51.771
And while my dad was out cold,
Barry was still fired up.

12:51.771 --> 12:53.314
Barry, enough!

12:53.314 --> 12:54.941
Let him have it. He's the one
stuck in the middle.

12:54.941 --> 12:56.276
In more ways than one.

12:56.276 --> 12:57.777
No one's talking to you,
Middle.

12:57.777 --> 12:59.654
Bar, just try to focus
on the good stuff, okay?

12:59.654 --> 13:01.072
We're going to Miami
together.

13:01.072 --> 13:02.949
[ Sighs ] You're right.
This is special.

13:02.949 --> 13:03.950
It really is.

13:03.950 --> 13:05.326
Not for me.

13:05.326 --> 13:07.203
But I want it to be
more than special.

13:07.203 --> 13:09.580
Which is why
you should be in first class.

13:09.580 --> 13:10.873
Outta my way.

13:10.873 --> 13:12.667
Crubbs a‐comin' through!

13:14.627 --> 13:17.130
So, look, there's something
I wanted to talk to you about.

13:17.130 --> 13:19.132
Um, this is kinda hard
for me.

13:19.132 --> 13:20.550
Surely,
you can't be serious.

13:20.550 --> 13:21.634
Actually, I am.

13:21.634 --> 13:23.428
And don't call you Shirley?
[ Chuckles ]

13:23.428 --> 13:25.388
I set you up,
but you missed that one.

13:25.388 --> 13:26.055
It feels like
you're missing it.

13:26.055 --> 13:28.725
Uh‐oh.
Trouble in nerd paradise?

13:28.725 --> 13:30.143
Barry, not now.

13:30.143 --> 13:32.020
You two should
hash things out in coach,

13:32.020 --> 13:34.480
where commoners like yourselves
stare out the window

13:34.480 --> 13:36.774
and dream of better lives
that will never materialize.

13:36.774 --> 13:38.568
Okay, Bar,
it's painfully clear

13:38.568 --> 13:40.653
you're insecure
about Ren's parents being rich.

13:40.653 --> 13:41.738
Am not.

13:41.738 --> 13:43.781
I don't care she has
a butler with a turban,

13:43.781 --> 13:44.907
like in "Annie."

13:44.907 --> 13:47.160
Just take your bickering
to the air slums.

13:47.160 --> 13:48.453
Never.

13:48.453 --> 13:51.039
Our unbreakable bond
will see us through anything.

13:51.039 --> 13:53.249
Brea, I'm sorry about
all the "Airplane!" jokes.

13:53.249 --> 13:54.876
So you'll stop
and we can talk?

13:54.876 --> 13:56.377
Of course.
What's on your mind?

13:56.377 --> 14:00.465
Hey, the fog
is getting thicker.

14:00.465 --> 14:02.675
One of the best
"Airplane!" bits.

14:02.675 --> 14:05.136
Barry knew I was powerless
to the comedy

14:05.136 --> 14:06.637
and had to finish the joke.

14:06.637 --> 14:09.307
And Leon's getting larger!

14:09.307 --> 14:11.017
I'm out.
I'm sorry!

14:11.017 --> 14:12.351
He set me up!

14:12.351 --> 14:14.020
But you gotta admit
it's a classic line.

14:14.020 --> 14:15.438
Enjoy first class,
Barry.

14:15.438 --> 14:17.231
Tell Ren I'll grab a cookie,
get the lay of the land,

14:17.231 --> 14:18.274
and send for her.

14:18.274 --> 14:19.984
While Barry was settling in,

14:19.984 --> 14:22.361
Erica wasn't letting Geoff
get comfortable.

14:22.361 --> 14:23.988
Oh, let me give you
this pillow.

14:25.448 --> 14:27.158
Sleepy time's over.
Now talk.

14:27.158 --> 14:28.326
There's nothing
to talk about!

14:28.326 --> 14:30.703
And now I got sandwich
on my Crockett pants!

14:30.703 --> 14:32.622
Erica could care less
about linen pants.

14:32.622 --> 14:34.499
She knew
she had to get Geoff to crack.

14:34.499 --> 14:36.000
Oh, no!
It's happening again!

14:36.000 --> 14:38.127
I know you know
what my mom is up to.

14:38.127 --> 14:40.338
Windpipe so tight, but also
our bodies are pressed so close.

14:40.338 --> 14:41.798
Conflicting feelings.

14:42.924 --> 14:44.258
Not to worry, folks.
[ Chuckles ]

14:44.258 --> 14:45.593
My boyfriend
got extreme diarrhea,

14:45.593 --> 14:47.220
but nothing
I can't handle.

14:47.220 --> 14:49.555
Geoff, do you need me to help
you with your extreme diarrhea?

14:49.555 --> 14:51.015
He's fine.

14:51.015 --> 14:53.434
He was holding something in,
but it's all out now.

14:53.434 --> 14:54.894
What the hell is wrong
with you people?

14:54.894 --> 14:55.853
That's an adult man!

14:55.853 --> 14:57.188
[ Groans ]

14:59.398 --> 15:00.566
Murray.

15:02.777 --> 15:05.113
Too many "Airplane!" jokes?
Impossible.

15:05.113 --> 15:07.532
What's impossible is how sweet
the sea beef is. [ Chuckles ]

15:07.532 --> 15:09.534
I'm gonna mow through three more
and get Ren.

15:09.534 --> 15:10.451
Yo, idiots.

15:10.451 --> 15:12.245
Erica?
How'd you get up here?

15:12.245 --> 15:14.038
Yeah, I defeated
the impenetrable security

15:14.038 --> 15:15.706
that is a curtain
with Velcro.

15:15.706 --> 15:18.918
Listen up, because the rest of
this trip is going to be hell.

15:19.877 --> 15:21.254
Murray, are you in there?

15:21.254 --> 15:22.630
[ Grunts ]
Ohh.

15:22.630 --> 15:23.923
Excuse me.

15:23.923 --> 15:25.591
Um, you've over‐served
my husband,

15:25.591 --> 15:27.385
and now he's trapped
in the bathroom.

15:27.385 --> 15:29.262
They're having a lot
of issues in there.

15:29.262 --> 15:31.305
[ Door handle rattles ]

15:31.305 --> 15:33.766
I can't get it open. Something's
wedged against the door.

15:33.766 --> 15:34.976
Must be my grumpy bear.

15:36.727 --> 15:37.979
[ Intercom chimes ]

15:37.979 --> 15:39.564
Beverly: Excuse me.

15:39.564 --> 15:41.816
Uh, is there a licensed
locksmith on the plane?

15:41.816 --> 15:44.694
[ Chuckles ] My husband
is trapped in our bathroom.

15:44.694 --> 15:47.071
[ Intercom dings ]
Well, you better get him out,
because he's the only one

15:47.071 --> 15:48.906
that's going with you
to that Bar Mitzvah.

15:48.906 --> 15:50.616
That's right.
We all know.

15:50.616 --> 15:52.785
Geoffrey, that was
our special bathroom secret!

15:52.785 --> 15:53.828
I'm sorry, Mrs. G.

15:53.828 --> 15:55.246
Also,
I would like to announce

15:55.246 --> 15:56.914
that I do not have
extreme diarrhea.

15:56.914 --> 15:59.709
No one cares about
your jacked‐up butt, Geoff!

15:59.709 --> 16:02.128
All they care about is that
our garbage mom lied to us!

16:02.128 --> 16:03.921
[ Intercom chimes ]

16:03.921 --> 16:06.549
Captain Roger:
Folks, the PA system is
for the cabin crew only.

16:06.549 --> 16:08.718
[ Intercom chimes ]
So, there's no beach.

16:08.718 --> 16:11.137
You still get to groove to
slightly out‐of‐date pop tunes

16:11.137 --> 16:12.263
with middle schoolers.

16:12.263 --> 16:15.016
No way! We're not going
anywhere with you!

16:15.016 --> 16:17.101
[ Door slams ]

16:17.101 --> 16:18.436
This is the captain.

16:18.436 --> 16:21.189
I can't fly with someone
trapped in the lavatory.

16:21.189 --> 16:23.357
We're making
an emergency landing.

16:23.357 --> 16:24.567
[ Passengers groan ]

16:24.567 --> 16:26.068
Hi.

16:26.068 --> 16:27.695
I'm Barry Goldberg, the rival
stag you've been smelling.

16:27.695 --> 16:28.821
Get back to your seats.

16:28.821 --> 16:30.907
Surely,
you can't be serious.

16:30.907 --> 16:32.992
If you don't,
I'll have you arrested.

16:32.992 --> 16:34.911
That's...
not the line.

16:37.622 --> 16:39.957
♪♪

16:39.957 --> 16:42.710
Adult Adam: Yep, the Goldbergs
were officially grounded

16:42.710 --> 16:45.463
and my mom's Bar Mitzvah dreams
all but over.

16:45.463 --> 16:47.673
Well, there's not another
flight out until tomorrow,

16:47.673 --> 16:49.383
and they won't let us
back on the plane,

16:49.383 --> 16:52.261
so [Sighs] I guess
we'll just go back home.

16:52.261 --> 16:54.680
It's what you all wanted,
anyway.

16:54.680 --> 16:56.724
Well, I'm not gonna feel bad
about this.

16:56.724 --> 16:59.352
Me, neither. If anything, she
should be apologizing to us.

16:59.352 --> 17:01.479
Bar Mitzvah or not,
it's still a trip to Miami.

17:01.479 --> 17:03.356
Yeah, which is ruining
our last week of summer.

17:03.356 --> 17:05.358
And because of that, I've
developed a drinking problem.

17:06.567 --> 17:07.777
[ Sighs ]

17:07.777 --> 17:09.237
That's from "Airplane!"
but it works here.

17:09.237 --> 17:10.529
It really doesn't.

17:10.529 --> 17:12.698
Look, Adam, I've been trying
to tell you something

17:12.698 --> 17:14.033
this whole flight,

17:14.033 --> 17:16.494
something I've been able to hide
our entire relationship.

17:16.494 --> 17:18.287
This happens a lot.
She's in love with me.

17:18.287 --> 17:19.330
Definitely not.

17:19.330 --> 17:20.790
It's this. [ Sighs ]

17:23.125 --> 17:24.627
So much metal.

17:24.627 --> 17:27.255
I have to wear this 10 hours
a day until my jaw's realigned.

17:27.255 --> 17:29.382
What an intense
chin strap.

17:29.382 --> 17:30.508
I was embarrassed
about it,

17:30.508 --> 17:32.426
but turns out
you're much more embarrassing.

17:32.426 --> 17:33.302
Is that cowhide?

17:33.302 --> 17:34.303
Well, I think
we can all agree

17:34.303 --> 17:35.304
this is our mom's fault.

17:35.304 --> 17:36.264
She's the worst.

17:36.264 --> 17:37.473
Or maybe you are.

17:37.473 --> 17:39.225
I‐I'm sorry,
but I was forced into

17:39.225 --> 17:40.893
that tiny sky bathroom
too many times.

17:40.893 --> 17:43.229
And all your mom wanted to do
was show you guys off.

17:43.229 --> 17:45.147
That tracks.
We are the best.

17:45.147 --> 17:47.525
It doesn't change the fact
that she tricked us into coming.

17:47.525 --> 17:48.609
I had to!

17:48.609 --> 17:50.152
Do you guys remember

17:50.152 --> 17:52.488
my cousin Larry's son's wedding
last year?

17:52.488 --> 17:54.740
Or Great Aunt Peggy's
funeral?

17:54.740 --> 17:56.951
Or the 90th birthday dinner
for Uncle Leonard?

17:56.951 --> 17:58.119
No.
Who?

17:58.119 --> 17:59.579
I have
a very busy schedule.

17:59.579 --> 18:01.664
Exactly, 'cause every time
there's a big event,

18:01.664 --> 18:04.166
none of you
will come with me.

18:04.166 --> 18:05.710
I've got these great kids,

18:05.710 --> 18:08.379
and all anyone knows about them
is that they never show up.

18:08.379 --> 18:10.423
Oh, man, she went
and made it real.

18:10.423 --> 18:13.843
Sometimes I can't believe
what I have ‐‐

18:13.843 --> 18:16.429
a son
who's gonna be a doctor...

18:16.429 --> 18:19.098
and another one
who's so imaginative,

18:19.098 --> 18:21.601
I'm constantly in awe...

18:21.601 --> 18:24.145
and a daughter
who's as smart and tough

18:24.145 --> 18:26.063
as any woman
I've ever known.

18:27.523 --> 18:30.192
Just want the rest of the family
to see what I have.

18:31.736 --> 18:33.154
[ Sighs ]

18:33.154 --> 18:34.488
[ Inhales sharply ]
Yikes.

18:34.488 --> 18:35.948
Yeah.

18:35.948 --> 18:37.575
I didn't know we had
an Uncle Leonard, either.

18:37.575 --> 18:39.493
Idiots,
we have to do something.

18:39.493 --> 18:40.411
But what?

18:40.411 --> 18:42.163
Sometimes
to make things right,

18:42.163 --> 18:43.873
you have to do something
very wrong.

18:43.873 --> 18:45.082
[ "Conga" plays ]

18:45.082 --> 18:46.626
With that, we unleashed

18:46.626 --> 18:48.878
our embarrassing,
shameful Goldberg fury.

18:48.878 --> 18:51.005
[ Voice breaking ]
You don't understand.
We have to get on that plane.

18:51.005 --> 18:52.423
Erica channeled
her inner Beverly

18:52.423 --> 18:55.176
by going nuclear
on customer service.

18:55.176 --> 18:57.928
Barry showed the captain
who was really in charge.

18:57.928 --> 19:00.348
And I weaponized
my love of "Airplane!"

19:00.348 --> 19:01.641
to wear down the gate agent.

19:01.641 --> 19:03.059
They love me.

19:03.059 --> 19:05.186
They really love me!

19:05.186 --> 19:07.021
Eh, I hope
that's what this is.

19:07.021 --> 19:09.440
And before long,
against all odds,

19:09.440 --> 19:11.651
we were on our way again
to Miami.

19:11.651 --> 19:14.612
Oh, no! They promised me
you wouldn't be back!

19:14.612 --> 19:16.822
Don't worry. You can take
the aisle if you want.

19:16.822 --> 19:18.491
I'd rather sit
next to my girlfriend.

19:18.491 --> 19:20.076
You sure you don't want to be
in first class?

19:20.076 --> 19:21.535
I don't know
what I was thinking.

19:21.535 --> 19:23.287
The seat next to you
is the best one there is.

19:23.287 --> 19:27.249
I'm out. I'll meet my birth
mother some other time.

19:27.249 --> 19:28.918
Thanks for
setting me straight.

19:28.918 --> 19:30.252
Hey,
that's what family does.

19:30.252 --> 19:31.962
I mean,
we're not family family,

19:31.962 --> 19:33.464
but I'm kind of
in your family, but ‐‐

19:33.464 --> 19:34.924
Shh.

19:34.924 --> 19:35.966
We're definitely family.

19:37.593 --> 19:38.844
For the record,

19:38.844 --> 19:40.513
I think you look adorable
in your headgear.

19:40.513 --> 19:41.639
Really?

19:41.639 --> 19:43.140
I hate it so much.

19:43.140 --> 19:45.935
It means we have even more
in common than we thought.

19:45.935 --> 19:47.061
You have headgear, too?

19:47.061 --> 19:49.063
And corrective lenses
for my lazy eye,

19:49.063 --> 19:50.773
special inserts
for my flat feet,

19:50.773 --> 19:52.483
and like
five different inhalers.

19:52.483 --> 19:54.235
I guess we're both
kind of a mess, then.

19:54.235 --> 19:56.028
As long as we're a mess
together.

19:57.238 --> 19:59.198
Oh. Right.
These don't recline.

19:59.198 --> 20:00.866
You can lean on me
instead.

20:00.866 --> 20:03.619
Roger, Roger.

20:03.619 --> 20:05.913
Turns out my love
of one little movie

20:05.913 --> 20:07.915
rubbed off
in an unexpected way.

20:07.915 --> 20:09.792
Ooh, first class, Murray!

20:09.792 --> 20:11.877
I could get used to this.

20:11.877 --> 20:14.463
Bevy, for you,
I'd fly to the moon.

20:14.463 --> 20:15.631
[ Engine whirs ]
What was that?!

20:15.631 --> 20:17.550
Just the engine.

20:17.550 --> 20:19.427
[ Dinging ]

20:19.427 --> 20:21.679
We're gonna need
all of your Chablises.

20:21.679 --> 20:24.640
With that,
we took to the skies ‐‐ again.

20:26.767 --> 20:29.937
And eventually, we made it
to Bradley's Bar Mitzvah.

20:29.937 --> 20:33.232
Sure, we traded the sun and
sand for bubbies and a buffet,

20:33.232 --> 20:34.817
but our mom was right.

20:34.817 --> 20:36.152
It was worth it.

20:36.152 --> 20:38.028
We had the best time ever

20:38.028 --> 20:40.948
because we had everything
we needed right there.

20:40.948 --> 20:42.658
We had each other.

20:42.658 --> 20:44.618
♪ Come on, shake your body,
baby, do the conga ♪

20:44.618 --> 20:46.912
♪♪

20:46.912 --> 20:49.457
With the power of wind,

20:49.457 --> 20:51.917
airplanes will always
hit the ground.

20:51.917 --> 20:53.794
Whee! We're flying!

20:53.794 --> 20:55.087
Gee, this is great.

20:55.087 --> 20:56.297
Hold on. Hold on.

20:56.297 --> 20:57.256
Aaaaah!

20:59.508 --> 21:02.595
What's this button do?
I told you
not to touch anything.

21:02.595 --> 21:04.305
Check it out! It's Otto
the Autopilot from "Airplane!"

21:04.305 --> 21:05.473
I'll take it from here!

21:05.473 --> 21:07.391
Do not touch the controls
with your toy!

21:07.391 --> 21:10.311
Toy?! This is a certified
replica movie prop.

21:10.311 --> 21:12.646
Attention, passengers,
this is your new top gun,

21:12.646 --> 21:14.899
Barry Goldberg,
call sign Strike Eagle Seven.

21:14.899 --> 21:16.734
Prepare yourselves
for a barrel roll.

21:16.734 --> 21:17.693
Get off that!

21:17.693 --> 21:19.111
Otto's got a leak.

21:19.111 --> 21:20.446
We need to make
an emergency landing ‐‐

21:20.446 --> 21:21.489
or get some Scotch tape.

21:21.489 --> 21:23.699
Look, this button says
"fuel dump."

21:23.699 --> 21:24.742
Ha ha ha! Dump!

21:24.742 --> 21:25.493
No!
